spacetimes other than Minkowski to restrict the values of  and .
For instance, if it turned out that the Bunch-Davies vacuum is the
only consistent vacuum in de Sitter spacetime, one could
directly compute the values of  and  for de Sitter and apply
them to non-de Sitter spacetimes.  However, at a phenomenological level
 and  could be -dependent, as happens for instance in the
"conventional" vacuum prescription.

 
