Let us emphasize again that the corrections in powers of  we
consider  here are not  directly related  to trans-Planckian  effects. 
Our corrections  become large on length  scales of the  Hubble radius. 
Their  origin  can be  ultimately  traced  back  to the  ambiguity  in
defining the notion  of a particle in an  expanding universe, when the
Compton  wavelength  has  a  size  comparable  to  the  Hubble  radius
.  Unknown trans-Planckian  physics only enter our
discussion  by preventing us  from taking  the limit  ,
making those corrections finite (but still small) rather than zero.

