satisfies the normalization condition ().

In  the limit where  the expansion  of the  universe is  "slow", one
expects  an  expansion in  the  number of  derivatives  to  be a  good
approximation to  solve for  . To perform  such an  expansion one
formally replaces   by  and expands  all quantities in a
power series in .  To th adiabatic order, only powers up to
