The  conventional vacuum  is  sometimes called  the adiabatic  vacuum,
since it agrees with the adiabatic  vacuum (of any order) in the limit
.   One   should  bear   in  mind  however   that  the
conventional vacuum  is only  a particular  adiabatic  vacuum in
the infinite set  of adiabatic vacua parametrized by  . Let us
note in  addition that  all the vacuum  prescriptions we  discuss here
also yield the adiabatic vacuum in the limit .


Hamiltonian diagonalization 

The Hamiltonian diagonalization vacuum(During the preparation
